coredata.dc:description:
Graphene based 2D materials after suitable modification may results into materials with strong nonlinear optical (NLO) responses. Here, incorporation of Au, and Ag nanoparticles (NPs) in graphene oxide (GO) nanosheet (GO_Au_Ag) is carried out for restructuring of its electronic bands. Reshuffling in the electronic band-to-band transitions and their relaxation process is achieved resulting into achievement of high NLO response in GO_Au_Ag than those of pure GO nanosheets, graphene quantum dot (GQD), and nitrogen doped GQD (N-GQD), by fs Z-scan technique. GO, GQD, and N-GQD, shows only two-photon absorption (2PA), with two times larger absorption coefficient (β) in N-GQD than that of GO and GQD. Interestingly, GO_Au_Ag nanocomposite exhibits simultaneous 2PA and three-photon absorption (3PA) under the excitation of the fs laser pulses. In the presence of prolongated relaxation time and transfer of charge between GO and metal’s state through excited state absorption (ESA), GO_Au_Ag showed a larger β value than N-GQD and the giant third order nonlinear susceptibility (χ 
      (3)
   ) of ∼10−9 (esu). Furthermore, GO_Au_Ag sample shows the optical limiting threshold of only 4.6 μJ/cm2, smaller than that of N-GQD.

ce:abstract-sec.ce:simple-para:
Graphene based 2D materials after suitable modification may results into materials with strong nonlinear optical (NLO) responses. Here, incorporation of Au, and Ag nanoparticles (NPs) in graphene oxide (GO) nanosheet (GO_Au_Ag) is carried out for restructuring of its electronic bands. Reshuffling in the electronic band-to-band transitions and their relaxation process is achieved resulting into achievement of high NLO response in GO_Au_Ag than those of pure GO nanosheets, graphene quantum dot (GQD), and nitrogen doped GQD (N-GQD), by fs Z-scan technique. GO, GQD, and N-GQD, shows only two-photon absorption (2PA), with two times larger absorption coefficient (β) in N-GQD than that of GO and GQD. Interestingly, GO_Au_Ag nanocomposite exhibits simultaneous 2PA and three-photon absorption (3PA) under the excitation of the fs laser pulses. In the presence of prolongated relaxation time and transfer of charge between GO and metal’s state through excited state absorption (ESA), GO_Au_Ag showed a larger β value than N-GQD and the giant third order nonlinear susceptibility (χ 
                        (3)
                     ) of ∼10−9 (esu). Furthermore, GO_Au_Ag sample shows the optical limiting threshold of only 4.6 μJ/cm2, smaller than that of N-GQD.

ce:section.ce:para:
To study the NLO properties of the synthesized samples, standard Z-scan measurements are performed in both the open aperture (OA) and closed aperture (CA) conditions in the femtosecond (fs) regime. The pump laser used is the pulsed laser radiation of wavelength 800 nm, pulse width of ∼ 150 fs, and operated at a repetition rate of 80 MHz. The beam waist (ω0
                     ) and the confocal parameter (Z0
                     ) of the used laser radiation are calculated to be 36 μm and 5 mm, respectively.
